name: PROOFPOINT TAP [Message Blocked - Spam]
description: This rule looks for Proofpoint Targeted Attack Protection message block events for messages identified as spam. This indicates a spam message that Proofpoint quarantined.

query: class=proofpoint_siemapi eventtype:`msgdlv*` threat=url category=spam NOT srcipv4:$exclusions.global.srcipv4
name: PROOFPOINT TAP [Message Delivered - Spam Link]
description: This rule looks for Proofpoint Targeted Attack Protection message delivery events for messages containing links identified as spam. This indicates that a message containing a spam link was delivered to a user.

query: class=proofpoint_siemapi eventtype:`msgdlv*` NOT threat=url NOT srcipv4:$exclusions.global.srcipv4
name: PROOFPOINT TAP [Message Delivered - Attachment/Text Threat]
description: This rule looks for Proofpoint Targeted Attack Protection message delivery events for messages containing malicious attachments or text-based threats such as executive impersonation. This indicates that a message containing malicious attachments or text was delivered to a user.

name: PROOFPOINT TAP [Click Blocked - Spam]
description: This rule looks for Proofpoint Targeted Attack Protection click block events for links identified as spam. This indicates that a user clicked a spam link that Proofpoint blocked.

query: class=proofpoint_siemapi eventtype:`clkblk*` NOT category=spam NOT srcipv4:$exclusions.global.srcipv4
name: PROOFPOINT TAP [Click Blocked - Malware/Phishing]
description: This rule looks for Proofpoint Targeted Attack Protection click block events for links identified as malware or phishing. This indicates that a user clicked a malware or phishing link that Proofpoint blocked.

name: PROOFPOINT TAP [Click Permitted - Spam]
description: This rule looks for Proofpoint Targeted Attack Protection click permit events for links identified as spam. This indicates that a user clicked a spam link that Proofpoint did not block.

query: class=proofpoint_siemapi eventtype:`clkper*` NOT category=spam NOT srcipv4:$exclusions.global.srcipv4
name: PROOFPOINT TAP [Click Permitted - Malware/Phishing]
description: This rule looks for Proofpoint Targeted Attack Protection click permit events for links identified as malware or phishing. This indicates that a user clicked a malware or phishing link that Proofpoint did not block.
